---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Option A — Melbourne" activeTab="melbourne">
  <div class="mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="tier-badge bg-melbourne/20 text-melbourne text-sm">A — Aspirational</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold">University of Melbourne</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mt-2">BSc (Mechanical Systems) &rarr; Master of Engineering (Mechanical)</p>
  </div>

  <blockquote>
    Top-20 globally for engineering. 5-year pathway. Most expensive option (~AUD 300k total tuition). Russian passport is not a problem.
    Realistic if Ivan ends Grade 11 with &ge; 3.5 GPA and SAT 1320+. Entry February 2029 (gap year) or July 2028 mid-year.
  </blockquote>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>The university</h2>
    <p>
      The University of Melbourne is consistently ranked <strong>top 15-30 worldwide</strong> for mechanical engineering (QS, THE, ARWU).
      Located in central Melbourne — large, cosmopolitan, English-speaking. Engineers Australia accredited, Washington Accord recognised
      (Ivan's degree would be portable to the US, UK, EU, Japan).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>The program</h2>
    <p>
      Melbourne uses the <strong>"Melbourne Model"</strong>: every undergraduate does a general bachelor's first,
      then a 2-3 year master's to specialise. There is <strong>no direct 4-year BE in Mechanical Engineering</strong>.
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Stage</th>
            <th>Degree</th>
            <th>Length</th>
            <th>Focus</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="text-melbourne font-bold">1</span></td>
            <td><strong>Bachelor of Science</strong> — Mechanical Systems major</td>
            <td>3 years</td>
            <td>Math, physics, mechanics, thermo, design</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="text-melbourne font-bold">2</span></td>
            <td><strong>Master of Engineering</strong> (Mechanical)</td>
            <td>2 years</td>
            <td>Professional accreditation — actual engineering qualification</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
      The Master is a guaranteed pathway provided the BSc is completed with the right major and a passing average — but it costs additional years of tuition.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Pros and cons</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card border-green-900/40">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-green-400 text-base">Pros</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Global brand — top-30 worldwide; opens doors anywhere</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> English-speaking environment, no Japanese needed</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Strong industry placements, Engineers Australia accredited</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Rolling admissions = early offers possible</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Personal essay + grades only — no interview, no portfolio</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Familiar Western-style university experience</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card border-red-900/40">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-red-400 text-base">Cons</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> <strong>5 years to graduate</strong>, not 4</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> <strong>~5&times; more expensive than Japan options</strong></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Must pass BSc + apply into the Master separately</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> February intake creates ~7-month gap</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Requires AP Calculus + AP Physics</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Living costs in Melbourne are high (~AUD 30k/yr)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Admission requirements</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Diploma</td><td>US High School Diploma (OCSI qualifies)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>GPA</td><td><strong>Unweighted GPA &ge; 3.5</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>SAT / ACT</td><td><strong>SAT 1320+</strong> or ACT 29+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>AP exams</td><td><strong>3 AP exams &ge; 4</strong>, including AP Calculus and AP Physics</td></tr>
          <tr><td>English</td><td>TOEFL iBT 79 or IELTS 6.5 (possible waiver for OCSI)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Personal statement</td><td>Required</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Interview / portfolio</td><td><strong>Not required</strong></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Cost</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">2026 published rates — verify in 2027</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Item</th><th>Per year</th><th>5-year total</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Tuition — BSc (years 1-3)</td><td>~AUD 53,888</td><td>AUD 161,664</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Tuition — Master (years 4-5)</td><td>~AUD 60,000</td><td>AUD 120,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Living costs</td><td>~AUD 32,000</td><td>AUD 160,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Health insurance (OSHC)</td><td>~AUD 700</td><td>AUD 3,500</td></tr>
          <tr class="font-bold text-white">
            <td>Approximate 5-year total</td>
            <td></td>
            <td class="text-melbourne">~AUD 445,000 (~USD 290,000)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-4">
      <h3 class="mt-0 text-base">Scholarships worth applying for</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 mb-0">
        <li><strong>Melbourne International Undergraduate Scholarship</strong> — AUD 10k up to full fees (auto-considered)</li>
        <li><strong>Faculty of Engineering and IT scholarships</strong> — merit-based, typically cover 10-25%</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Application timeline</h2>
    <div class="mermaid-container">
      <pre class="mermaid">
gantt
    title  Melbourne — Application Timeline (2028/29 entry)
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    axisFormat  %b %Y

    section Preparation
    SAT prep                          :2026-09-01, 240d
    PSAT diagnostic                   :milestone, 2026-10-14, 0d
    AP Calc AB + AP Physics (G11)     :2026-08-17, 280d
    First SAT (target 1320+)          :milestone, 2027-05-01, 0d
    TOEFL iBT                         :milestone, 2027-07-15, 0d
    SAT retake if needed              :milestone, 2027-10-02, 0d

    section Application
    Apply online (rolling)            :2027-08-01, 180d
    Personal statement draft 1        :2027-09-01, 30d
    Submit complete application       :milestone, 2027-11-15, 0d
    Final submission deadline (Feb)   :milestone, 2028-02-01, 0d

    section Decision & Enrolment
    Offer received (4-6 wk after sub) :2027-12-15, 45d
    Accept offer + deposit            :milestone, 2028-03-01, 0d
    Student visa (subclass 500)       :2028-04-01, 90d
    Confirm OSHC + accommodation      :2028-07-01, 60d
    Semester 1, 2029 begins           :milestone, 2029-02-26, 0d
      </pre>
    </div>

    <h3>Key dates</h3>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Sep 2026</td><td>Start SAT prep; lock in AP Calc + AP Physics for Grade 11</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Oct 14, 2026</td><td>Take PSAT (diagnostic)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">May 2027</td><td>Take first SAT — target 1320+</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Jul 2027</td><td>Take TOEFL iBT</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Aug 1, 2027</td><td>Melbourne 2028 intake applications open</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Sep 2027</td><td>Begin personal statement (5 drafts minimum)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Oct 2027</td><td>SAT retake if first attempt &lt; 1320</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Nov 15, 2027</td><td>Target submission date</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Dec '27 – Feb '28</td><td>Rolling offer notification (4-6 weeks after submission)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Mar 2028</td><td>Accept offer + pay deposit</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Apr-Jun 2028</td><td>Lodge student visa application (subclass 500)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Feb 26, 2029</td><td>Semester 1 starts</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-4 border-melbourne/30">
      <h4 class="mt-0 text-base text-melbourne">Alternative — Mid-year intake (July 2028)</h4>
      <p class="text-sm mb-0">
        Melbourne offers a <strong>July (Semester 2) intake</strong> which would let Ivan start ~6 weeks after graduation with no gap year.
        Fewer courses are available at mid-year entry, and the BSc with Mechanical Systems major is sometimes restricted.
        <strong>Check this on the BSc course page when applications open in 2027.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Application checklist</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>Confirm OCSI is accredited (ACSI / WASC) — yes, OCSI is ACSI-accredited</li>
      <li>Request official transcript from OCSI (Grade 9-11 first, Grade 12 first semester later)</li>
      <li>Take SAT — target 1320+ (1450+ ideal)</li>
      <li>Take TOEFL iBT — target 90+</li>
      <li>AP scores: Calculus + Physics + one more, all 4+</li>
      <li>Two academic references</li>
      <li>Personal statement: 500-1,000 words</li>
      <li>CV / activities list</li>
      <li>Passport scan (Russian) + Japanese residence card</li>
      <li>Submit online application</li>
      <li>Pay application fee (~AUD 100)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Russian passport — practical notes</h2>
    <div class="card border-surface-600">
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
        <li>Australia has <strong>no visa ban</strong> for Russian nationals.</li>
        <li>Student visa: subclass 500. Standard documentation. Expect 4-12 weeks processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Pay tuition deposit from a Japan-based bank account, not Russia.</strong> SWIFT routing from Russian banks is restricted post-2022.</li>
        <li>On arrival in Melbourne, opening an Australian bank account as a Russian national has occasionally been refused at certain banks — CommBank and ANZ have been workable.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Realistic verdict</h2>
    <div class="card border-melbourne/30">
      <p class="mb-3">Melbourne is genuinely achievable if Ivan:</p>
      <ol class="text-sm space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Locks in AP Calculus + AP Physics + AP Chemistry for Grade 11</li>
        <li>Hits SAT &ge; 1320 (realistically targets 1400+ to be safe)</li>
        <li>Hits TOEFL iBT &ge; 80 (targets 95+)</li>
        <li>Maintains unweighted GPA &ge; 3.5 across Grade 11 and Grade 12 first semester</li>
        <li>Writes a personal statement connecting an actual project or interest to mechanical engineering</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-0">
        It is <strong>not</strong> achievable if Grade 11 grades slip into the 3.0 range or if AP courses are skipped.
        The real cost-benefit question: is the Melbourne brand worth ~USD 240,000 <em>more</em> than Waseda over 5 years?
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
